article.headline: Prairie View 87, Paul Quinn 72
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Anthony Oha had 18 points and nine rebounds as Prairie View A&M defeated Paul Quinn 87-72 Friday night. Prairie View (1-0) outscored Paul Quinn (0-1) 44-25 in the second half. Damien Chisholm dropped in 20 points for Paul Quinn, which shot only 33 percent after halftime. Clifford Franks had 14 points and eight rebounds off the bench for Prairie View A&M. The Panthers also got 13 points from Jeremy Wiley. Alonzo Butler had 17 points and Amahad Jennings had 13 for Paul Quinn. Paul Quinn shot 51 percent in the first half as it led 47-43 at halftime. But the Tigers lost their lead, in part to poor shooting, and they turned the ball over 27 times.
